The paper discusses the security implications of DDoS prevention in the context of online elections, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the infrastructure and deployment of the DDoS protection service, which could fall under distributed systems (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also touches on the potential for cyber attacks and nation-state interference, which could fall under cybercrime (cs.CY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
